Template: supermon-ng/configure-apache
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Configure Apache for Supermon-ng?
 Automatically enable required Apache modules, install the supermon-ng site
 configuration under /etc/apache2/sites-available/, and reload Apache.
 .
 Choose "No" if you use nginx or manage Apache vhosts yourself.

Template: supermon-ng/disable-default-sites
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Disable default Apache sites?
 Disable the Debian default sites (000-default and default-ssl) so
 Supermon-ng can serve HTTP/HTTPS on ports 80 and 443.

Template: supermon-ng/refresh-apache-site
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Regenerate Apache site configuration?
 Replace /etc/apache2/sites-available/supermon-ng.conf with a newly
 generated configuration from your current .env settings.
 .
 Only choose "Yes" if you want to discard manual edits to that file.
